WEBVTT

00:01.218 --> 00:01.679
Good morning.

00:03.603 --> 00:07.249
So this morning we are, I'm Adam, this is Lucy.

00:08.231 --> 00:14.543
This morning we're continuing our Root Rooted series and we're looking at fellowship, find your people and David Nickfort up.

00:14.563 --> 00:18.972
It was a good idea because me Lucy and Marcia are kind of heading up life groups.

00:18.992 --> 00:21.557
It was appropriate that we talk to you about that topic.

00:22.699 --> 00:24.402
Me and Lucy were joking.

00:24.450 --> 00:28.596
Given that we're kind of tag teaming this, what does when one person's talking, what does he have a person do?

00:29.617 --> 00:33.042
Like, like interpretive dance, like get my aing out.

00:34.184 --> 00:37.268
So, I don't know, we'll look, one of us will look around while the other one's talking.

00:38.711 --> 00:43.918
So the goal of this series is all based on Psalm 1, date which Dave raised last week.

00:44.599 --> 00:49.426
And the idea is that we have to be like trees that are planted by streams of living water.

00:49.730 --> 00:55.238
And last week they've looked at how this can be done in a larger setting gathered environments like on a Sunday morning.

00:55.639 --> 01:00.526
So this morning we're going to be looking at I guess more intimate environments and small groups.

01:02.029 --> 01:13.586
Yeah, so today we want to look at fellowship in a broader setting and our goal is that by the end that we can each go away and look to action something in our relationships that is Jesus centred.

01:13.762 --> 01:16.285
So that might mean signing up to a life group.

01:16.525 --> 01:24.475
It might mean speaking to someone about a one to one meeting up or just being more intentional in your already existing spiritual friendships.

01:25.536 --> 01:34.547
So we just don't want this morning to just be theoretical, but we do want to offer a little bit of teaching to encourage you to take steps that will strengthen your roots in God.

01:36.209 --> 01:37.651
So what is fellowship?

01:37.791 --> 01:40.594
The idea of fellowship a bit like cover words is

01:40.674 --> 01:43.920
partly lost when you compare it to what the Bible teaches about a word fellowship.

01:44.521 --> 01:51.715
We're actually going to use slightly different words just to freshen things up, which is spiritual friendship.

01:51.896 --> 01:59.811
Because when you say the word fellowship, a lot of people might think of coffee mornings, or you'll go around to a little interest on one's house and say, I had fantastic fellowship at their house.

02:00.372 --> 02:01.394
And that's not

02:01.762 --> 02:04.489
wrong but it's just not the full picture of what the Bible says.

02:05.632 --> 02:14.514
Galatians 6 verse 2 says we should carry each other's burdens and in this way you will fulfill the law of Christ.

02:14.594 --> 02:17.399
I was like looking at what the meaning of one of the words means.

02:17.419 --> 02:20.123
So that word burden in the Greek is different.

02:20.324 --> 02:23.409
You see other words burden in New Testament and it's the different Greek word.

02:24.110 --> 02:30.541
And the other uses talk about when you have an oxen that was laden with a burden and it was measured out.

02:31.082 --> 02:34.608
Whereas this word doesn't have any idea of it being measured out.

02:34.849 --> 02:40.338
So a burden we might have to be carrying might be too heavy for us.

02:41.282 --> 02:43.665
It may not be possible to carry it on our own.

02:43.825 --> 02:45.286
We have to carry each other's burdens.

02:47.008 --> 02:47.108
Yeah.

02:50.432 --> 02:54.757
So why else is fellowship or spiritual friendship with other believers so important?

02:55.397 --> 02:58.421
Other than, because it's the only way we can carry our burdens.

02:59.542 --> 03:04.467
So by the time we're near the end of Genesis 2, God has made the universe, including Adam.

03:05.248 --> 03:07.090
Sin has not entered the world yet.

03:07.234 --> 03:11.118
And as a result, God taught many times about how he is made is good.

03:11.598 --> 03:13.420
And it even calls Adam very good.

03:14.281 --> 03:16.363
But there's one thing that he says is not good.

03:16.944 --> 03:21.929
Verse 18 reads, the Lord God said, it is not good for man to be alone.

03:23.150 --> 03:26.013
And this is fascinating because nothing has been corrupted yet.

03:26.633 --> 03:28.815
And still God says something is not good.

03:29.976 --> 03:35.602
Or to put it another way, just making Adam even in a place where there was no sin at all was not enough.

03:36.418 --> 03:40.023
Quite often, when this verse is used, it's given a narrow interpretation.

03:40.203 --> 03:42.065
We hear it in marriage ceremonies a lot.

03:42.906 --> 03:47.032
God does create Eve as a wife, but the principle is far broader than this.

03:47.793 --> 03:51.438
It's about community, relationship, spiritual friendship.

03:52.880 --> 03:58.968
And of course, there won't be marriage in heaven, not between humans, only with God and his bride of church.

04:00.009 --> 04:03.954
In Mark chapter 12 verse 25, Jesus says,

04:04.098 --> 04:07.383
When the dead rise, they will neither marry nor be given in marriage.

04:07.563 --> 04:08.885
They will be likely angels in heaven.

04:10.448 --> 04:15.455
The Christian brothers and sisters we know now, however, will be in fellowship with us forever after death.

04:17.158 --> 04:30.338
So if Eden is a foreshadowing of the new earth to come and in it, God says there is something not good about being alone and being together as believers is a fundamental part of eternity.

04:31.059 --> 04:32.882
And so it should be now.

04:32.962 --> 04:34.644
We need fellowship.

04:34.684 --> 04:35.925
We need spiritual friendship.

04:36.566 --> 04:41.873
All the time, even if we don't currently realize it, I've stolen this illustration from Tim Keller.

04:41.893 --> 04:42.994
I didn't make it up.

04:43.014 --> 04:46.538
But no one walks around thinking, I love air.

04:47.159 --> 04:49.582
No one goes, oh, thanks for that breath.

04:50.182 --> 04:50.883
Thanks for that breath.

04:51.644 --> 04:56.690
We just do it subconsciously until we're underwater and suddenly...

04:56.770 --> 05:01.895
Even just having a cold, not being able to breathe through your nose, you realise how much you need to breathe.

05:02.355 --> 05:04.697
And spiritual friendship fellowship is very similar.

05:06.019 --> 05:10.243
Often we don't realise how much we need it until things turn, things get bad.

05:10.763 --> 05:17.469
And the problem is for deep spiritual friendship with Christians, we can't just click our fingers and have that intimacy when we need it.

05:17.489 --> 05:21.453
It needs to be cultivated like Dave said last week before we run into trouble.

05:23.375 --> 05:26.578
So Ecclesiastes 4 of verses 9 to 12 says,

05:26.722 --> 05:30.189
Two are better than one because they have a good return for their labour.

05:30.950 --> 05:37.142
If either of them falls down, one can help the other up, but pity anyone who falls and has no one to help them up.

05:37.984 --> 05:42.432
Also, if two lie down together, they will keep warm, but how can one keep warm alone?

05:43.094 --> 05:46.200
Though one may be overpowered, two can defend themselves.

05:46.861 --> 05:49.426
A chord of three strands is not quickly broken.

05:50.818 --> 05:58.110
We need spiritual friendship, not just any friendship, but the fellowship among believers who are unified by that third called Christ.

05:58.751 --> 06:01.095
We need to have people who can help us up when we fall.

06:02.798 --> 06:08.808
Spiritual friendship or fellowship is also a good combat to our sinfulness and tendency to self-justify.

06:09.869 --> 06:11.592
Dietrich Bonhoeffer puts it well.

06:12.554 --> 06:17.522
The more isolated a person is, the more destructive will be the power of his sin over him.

06:18.114 --> 06:22.540
And the more deeply he becomes involved in it, the more disastrous is his isolation.

06:23.501 --> 06:30.791
But since the confession of sin is made in the presence of a Christian brother, the last stronghold of self-justification is abandoned.

06:32.673 --> 06:35.817
When we're not open with our faults, we tend to want to self-justify.

06:36.458 --> 06:38.781
Certainly it's something that me and Adam do.

06:38.801 --> 06:42.546
And even sharing your faults in marriage alone sometimes isn't enough.

06:42.690 --> 06:48.399
because you're so unified and one that you still lean towards trying to tell yourself something isn't as bad as it is.

06:49.360 --> 06:56.872
The beauty of our church's diversity is that others can take a more objective view of our lives and keep us honest, keep us accountable.

06:58.674 --> 07:08.850
The act of vulnerability and spiritual friendship also helps in the opposite way, not just to prevent us from wrongly patting ourselves on the back, but to help us not wrongly tell ourselves off.

07:09.474 --> 07:16.222
It can count to self-condemnation and self-criticism through encouraging one another and offering Jesus' message of grace.

07:17.243 --> 07:22.770
I don't know about you, but I find it is often easier to show grace to others than it is to myself.

07:24.632 --> 07:30.298
I have one particular friend, her name's Beth, and this is what she has offered me for the last 15 years.

07:31.260 --> 07:36.786
We don't live physically close, but we make sure we maintain spiritual closeness by regular calls and visits.

07:37.506 --> 07:47.119
We've often followed devotionals together, being able to spare each other on by sharing our thoughts via what's up, or sharing book quotes to each other, or worship songs we're really connecting with.

07:48.100 --> 07:50.563
We regularly ask each other, how is your soul?

07:52.045 --> 07:58.854
It's an interesting one to answer, but we answer it however we want, and are willing to challenge moments of compromise or wrong attitudes.

08:00.095 --> 08:02.098
We are not yes men to each other.

08:02.338 --> 08:07.526
but we are yes men to Jesus who have given each other permission to speak into our lives.

08:08.748 --> 08:16.640
Proverbs 27 verse 17 says, as I am sharpens iron, so one person sharpens another and that's definitely my experience.

08:17.822 --> 08:22.148
Through my spiritual friendship, fellowship with Beth, I've grown in my faith.

08:22.949 --> 08:26.735
I've had someone who kept Jesus light shining to me during the dark times.

08:27.556 --> 08:31.282
Someone who lovingly gently challenged me when my thinking was wrong.

08:31.682 --> 08:35.969
and someone who demonstrated God's grace to me when I couldn't find it myself.

08:38.874 --> 08:41.038
Surely the answer to how his soul is saved.

08:45.105 --> 08:50.354
So back to my reasons for fellowship, God desires it.

08:50.594 --> 08:51.895
I love this idea.

08:51.995 --> 09:02.986
The ache for community that the original Adam will have had, and God recognized by saying it's not good for man to be alone, is the only ache that existed before sin entered the world.

09:04.347 --> 09:07.731
All of the aches we might have for things are because of a fall.

09:09.312 --> 09:17.260
If you are aching for spiritual friendship, in other words, if you are lonely, that desire to know and be known isn't dysfunctional.

09:17.520 --> 09:19.442
Being lonely is not dysfunctional.

09:19.650 --> 09:20.611
It's a sign of help.

09:22.735 --> 09:23.856
There's not anything wrong with you.

09:25.899 --> 09:28.723
I feel like I just need to pause for a second there.

09:30.326 --> 09:35.694
The root feeling of loneliness means that your heart aligns with God's heart on the matter.

09:36.896 --> 09:37.977
It's not good to be alone.

09:39.680 --> 09:43.986
We are made to be in community, to have true spiritual friendship.

09:44.546 --> 09:49.471
We have to be careful when we talk about loneliness because it's not always simple, it's not always caused by one thing.

09:50.432 --> 09:56.858
The reason why someone might feel lonely can be because of their circumstances or it can be because of their actions.

09:57.658 --> 10:03.204
It might be for reasons they brought about or others brought about, but regardless, feeling is to be human.

10:04.385 --> 10:14.194
And what some of us do, what I do, if I'm honest, is to cope with sometimes feeling lonely is that you learn to not need others.

10:14.690 --> 10:17.112
And I don't think it's usually a conscious thing.

10:17.132 --> 10:19.855
No one walks around thinking, I will not need anyone today.

10:21.216 --> 10:24.660
But we do develop coping habits that mean that we don't depend on others.

10:25.561 --> 10:28.203
And I think we often suffer more hardship.

10:29.424 --> 10:35.951
We choose to suffer more hardship rather than be alternative of making ourselves vulnerable and having spiritual friendship.

10:37.232 --> 10:38.493
We might even think we're doing a good thing.

10:38.533 --> 10:43.698
Might say it's in the name of independence or not being a burden on others, but

10:44.738 --> 10:54.488
There is some truth in the fact that only God is truly dependable, but he designed life to be lived in community, and he often supports us through other people.

10:55.789 --> 10:58.692
So, you've probably heard this quote before, but C.S.

10:58.712 --> 11:03.897
Lewis talks about love, and he says, to love at all is to be vulnerable.

11:04.338 --> 11:06.760
Love anything in your heart will be wrong and possibly broken.

11:07.921 --> 11:12.466
If you want to make sure of keeping it intact, you must give it to no one, not even an animal.

11:12.770 --> 11:19.781
Wrap it carefully round with hobbies and little luxuries, avoid all entanglements, lock it up safe in the casket or coffin of your selfishness.

11:20.843 --> 11:32.140
But in that casket, safe, dark, motionless, airless, it will change, it will not be broken, it will become unbreakable, impenetrable, irredeemable, to love is to be vulnerable.

11:33.623 --> 11:35.987
And I suggest spiritual friendship is exactly the same.

11:37.068 --> 11:40.754
To need of us is to risk being let down, disappointed,

11:41.634 --> 11:45.939
where a problem is when we choose self-sufficiency, we move away from the heart of God.

11:45.959 --> 11:50.484
And as that verse in Galatians suggests, we can't carry our own burdens.

11:52.166 --> 11:58.153
Even Jesus, who did not need anyone else, chose to share his life with 12 individuals.

11:58.854 --> 12:00.256
He shared everything with them.

12:00.596 --> 12:02.318
And in return, one of them betrayed him.

12:02.358 --> 12:04.201
They constantly misunderstood him.

12:04.241 --> 12:08.786
They questioned what he was doing at every turn.

12:09.026 --> 12:12.429
but he still chose their friendship fellowship, even to the one who would turn on him.

12:16.153 --> 12:18.595
So how can we grow in spiritual friendship?

12:19.616 --> 12:23.721
The New Testament Greek word coinonia means sharing.

12:24.341 --> 12:28.005
God wants us as a community of believers to share everything.

12:30.027 --> 12:31.348
So what do we share?

12:31.388 --> 12:37.394
We share our time in a culture of, sorry, in a culture of busyness,

12:37.538 --> 12:42.264
God asks, we are open-handed with who we spend our time with.

12:42.284 --> 12:51.595
We are to share our things, resisting the temptation to think that just because we worked hard to earn money and buy things, we own them in any meaningful sense.

12:52.216 --> 12:54.599
The earth is the Lord and everything in it.

12:56.281 --> 13:02.328
We're to share our emotions, trusting people with how we're really feeling when people ask you how you are in us in the morning, how do you answer?

13:02.349 --> 13:06.834
Not being guarded all the time, not worrying about what they might think of you.

13:07.938 --> 13:13.625
and we are to share our decisions, being willing to change our mind on things when others give another perspective.

13:15.087 --> 13:16.349
There is attention here, too.

13:16.749 --> 13:20.894
Spiritual friendship, fellowship, is both discovered and it's made.

13:21.715 --> 13:27.703
It's not just something you discover but also make, and it's not something that you only make, it has to be discovered.

13:28.904 --> 13:34.091
It's discovered because all true friendship that lasts has a shared interest or circumstance.

13:34.832 --> 13:36.594
To quote C. S. Lewis again,

13:36.898 --> 13:39.623
Those people who simply want friends can never make any.

13:40.124 --> 13:44.172
The very condition of having friends is that we should want something else besides friends.

13:44.974 --> 13:49.202
The typical expression of the beginning of friendship would be something like, what?

13:49.602 --> 13:50.023
You too.

13:50.083 --> 13:51.707
I thought I was the only one.

13:51.767 --> 13:59.762
The greatest thing about our faith is that it is the greatest shared interest or circumstance to ever exist.

13:59.938 --> 14:05.884
that we, in this room today and in the church wider, we are united in our love for Christ.

14:06.324 --> 14:09.848
We have that shared interest, that shared circumstance through Him.

14:10.688 --> 14:17.195
So though we may share nothing else, we do share the most fundamental life-changing truth and that is enough.

14:18.456 --> 14:21.779
So a few examples, I don't think I've seen Denise here this morning.

14:23.581 --> 14:24.161
No, she is.

14:24.181 --> 14:26.344
I don't think she is, but I'm gonna talk about Denise.

14:26.364 --> 14:28.946
So mine and Denise's friendship,

14:29.090 --> 14:35.420
Denise has been coming to our small group for seven, eight years, every week.

14:36.001 --> 14:39.467
And me and Denise have very little in common, apart from our faith.

14:39.567 --> 14:40.669
We're at different life stages.

14:40.689 --> 14:41.811
We have different interests.

14:42.572 --> 14:43.273
She hates cheese.

14:43.353 --> 14:43.894
I love cheese.

14:45.777 --> 14:46.578
She's very important.

14:48.501 --> 14:56.274
But we have really beautiful friendship because we both love cheeses and we both want to be more like cheeses.

14:56.610 --> 15:09.524
She is so open with how she is and I try to be too, but actually I value my friendship with Denise more than someone who might not know the Lord who shares everything in common with I do with me.

15:11.546 --> 15:14.169
At the same time, spiritual friendship has to be made.

15:14.730 --> 15:16.852
You have to be intentional to nurture it.

15:17.693 --> 15:22.418
We can let the excuse of other parts of our life get in the way and it can fall by the wayside.

15:23.650 --> 15:28.006
So another example, sorry Andrew, is my friendship with Andrew memory.

15:28.106 --> 15:32.562
So Andrew since 2011, 2012 has

15:32.770 --> 15:35.413
every six to eight weeks, it's usually you but messages me.

15:35.433 --> 15:37.114
I try and remember to.

15:37.174 --> 15:38.736
He'll message me and say, do you want to go for a walk?

15:38.876 --> 15:45.643
And we'll go for a walk every six a.m. And it means we've got to sacrifice our time and with little kids, our sleep as well.

15:46.944 --> 15:51.208
But how Andrew has been faithful in just messaging me, it's actually girded.

15:51.248 --> 15:55.052
My life is last 10 years because it's meant that there's been an opportunity to be vulnerable.

15:56.113 --> 15:56.914
We don't have an agenda.

15:56.954 --> 16:00.978
It's not like he sends me a tinnery that wouldn't surprise me.

16:01.058 --> 16:04.302
We just talk about how life is and how our faith is.

16:06.285 --> 16:07.927
But that's also required being intentional.

16:09.749 --> 16:15.317
So to offer some more examples, to get you also thinking about what spiritual friendship might look like for you.

16:17.279 --> 16:18.381
Life groups, sorry.

16:19.762 --> 16:24.008
So Sunday morning gatherings are fundamental to being the body of Christ, but they aren't enough.

16:24.989 --> 16:28.754
It's difficult to have real depth and intimacy with others on a Sunday morning.

16:29.666 --> 16:31.410
alone in a group of 100 people.

16:32.472 --> 16:38.003
There is something special about regular time with the same people every week or every fortnight.

16:39.065 --> 16:43.374
It's why me and Lucy have always felt that we had to prioritise leading a small group when other things have got harder.

16:43.394 --> 16:45.618
We've had to put other stuff on the back burner.

16:46.658 --> 16:54.129
So there's also other gatherings of Christians, and I'm sure there'll be other situations like this, but just to give you an example of what I know.

16:54.149 --> 17:05.266
I'm part of an online community called the Faith Filled Collective, which is a group of light-minded women who use teaching from neuroscience, psychology stuff, to grow in our faith.

17:05.887 --> 17:10.674
And we have a monthly webinar, a connection call, and an ongoing WhatsApp group.

17:10.754 --> 17:13.338
It's open to any woman with a monthly subscription fee.

17:14.139 --> 17:18.446
Come and talk to me more at the end if that sounds like something you'd be interested in and I'll be happy to tell you more.

17:18.867 --> 17:25.116
But like I say, I think there are other kind of online connected, faith-based groups that you can find out.

17:26.899 --> 17:30.745
Or maybe there's one-on-one regular meet-ups with someone that can be really important.

17:31.486 --> 17:34.451
Maybe with someone who shares some of your life circumstances, but not others.

17:34.491 --> 17:38.898
Maybe someone who's a bit further ahead than you or just has a different perspective.

17:39.106 --> 17:47.681
creating space to challenge each other and checking in with whether you've implemented what you've said you would last time and sharing answers to prayer.

17:49.544 --> 17:54.994
So maybe just someone you can check in with as though we're a spiritual MOT but more than once a year.

17:55.138 --> 18:00.105
We've talked in church before about spiritual, emotional, physical scales.

18:00.626 --> 18:08.017
And they're a really good starting point to open up deeper conversations, if you feel how is your soul is a bit intense and broad.

18:08.979 --> 18:12.805
So you give yourself a number or a number range, really the number doesn't matter.

18:13.305 --> 18:19.695
The point is that it's some kind of marking out a 10 for how you're doing spiritually, emotionally and physically.

18:20.176 --> 18:21.778
And then you use it to open up

18:21.954 --> 18:26.540
board of conversations as why you're feeling like that, what you could do to change it and so on.

18:28.363 --> 18:39.699
Or even alpha, one of the reasons alpha so powerful is because you come with somebody and you are journeying your questions about life and faith with people and that's why it's always good to come with someone.

18:41.361 --> 18:45.767
Or reading a Christian book together, meet up with one or two other people to discuss it.

18:45.927 --> 18:47.890
I've done this in the past, it helps you

18:48.290 --> 18:54.560
take time to read the book in between, and then also have a space to ask questions and just share your thoughts.

18:57.124 --> 19:04.955
We've never read a book together here, I mean, it's funny to other people, but it's about... Maybe we will.

19:05.536 --> 19:06.177
Maybe we should.

19:06.298 --> 19:09.282
So to conclude... That's because we need two copies of the book.

19:09.683 --> 19:10.063
That's true.

19:10.344 --> 19:11.626
We read it one after the other.

19:14.310 --> 19:17.074
In order to be rooted in Christ and flourishing,

19:17.250 --> 19:22.157
we have to be rooted in one another, in community, in spiritual friendship.

19:22.177 --> 19:25.441
It's God's heart that we are true, in true and intimate community of other people.

19:27.184 --> 19:30.488
Loneliness is a symptom, but you share God's heart, not that you are dysfunctional.

19:31.690 --> 19:36.957
We need fellowship and it means sharing everything and having a courage to try again.

19:37.859 --> 19:40.943
And fellowship is both discovered and made.

19:42.866 --> 19:45.970
So we want to leave you with a question or are there a few questions?

19:46.082 --> 19:49.888
How can you pursue spiritual friendship more starting today?

19:51.030 --> 19:52.973
What do you need to help facilitate this?

19:54.195 --> 19:57.721
Are there walls of self-sufficiency that you need to ask God to knock down?

19:57.761 --> 20:02.990
Are there past hurts that mean you're scared to start again which you could spend some time giving to God?

20:03.991 --> 20:07.257
Do you just need to be more intentional this year with your Christian friends?

20:08.218 --> 20:11.023
Can you join on more regularly attend a life group?

20:12.465 --> 20:13.106
This week,

20:13.378 --> 20:17.848
Can you choose one person or one group and make one change?

20:20.254 --> 20:27.731
So there's a bit of a change to a norm and we didn't plan this, but we thought rather than having ministry time, we would just try and have five.

20:28.212 --> 20:28.794
What time is it?

20:28.834 --> 20:30.738
There we go.

20:30.850 --> 20:37.862
Yeah, five or so minutes of intentional time space where you can be thinking about an action you might want to take.

20:38.523 --> 20:41.649
You could go across the room and see if there's someone you could meet up with.

20:43.011 --> 20:44.193
You could send a message to someone.

20:44.233 --> 20:48.060
You already share friendship with a range of time to catch up with them.

20:48.761 --> 20:49.964
You could sign up to a life group.

20:50.625 --> 20:51.827
You can invite someone to lunch today.

20:51.887 --> 20:55.954
